==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Miliolite
<hw>Mil"i*o*lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld>
<def>A fossil shell of, or similar to, the genus
<gen>Miliola</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Miliolite</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Miliolite
<hw>Mil"i*o*lite</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>The same
<er>Miliolitic</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Miliolite limestone</b></col> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>, <cd>a
building stone, one of the group of the Paris basin, almost entirely
made up of many-chambered microscopic shells.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Miliolitic</ent>⟦br⟧
